!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

worker /ˈwɜːkə/

(workers) 

1. N-COUNT A particular kind of worker does the kind of work mentioned. 人员 

例： She ate her sandwich alongside several other office workers taking their break. 她在其他几位正在休息的办公室人员旁边吃自己的三明治。 

2. N-COUNT Workers are people who are employed in industry or business and who are not managers. 工人; 员工 

例： Wages have been frozen and workers laid off. 工资已被冻结，员工们下岗了。 

3. N-COUNT You can use worker to say how well or badly someone works. 工作 (好或坏) 的人 

例： He is a hard worker and a skilled gardener. 他是一个工作努力的人，一个技艺娴熟的园艺工。 

4.  →  see also social worker

</div>

